OL,3,CHousehold energy bills about to fall
OL,4,Cto lowest point in two years
OL,6,FThe average household energy bill is
OL,7,Fto fall to its lowest point in two
OL,8,Fyears from next month after Ofgem
OL,9,Flowered its price cap in response to
OL,10,Fwholesale prices.
OL,12,FIn some long-awaited good news for
OL,13,Fenergy customers, the regulator is
OL,14,Fdropping its price cap by 12.3% from
OL,15,Fthe current #1,928 for a typical dual
OL,16,Ffuel household in England, Scotland
OL,17,Fand Wales to #1,690, a drop of #238
OL,18,Fover the course of a year or around
OL,19,F#20 a month.
