OL,3,CHousehold energy bills about to fall
OL,4,Cto lowest point in two years
OL,6,FThe average household on a standard
OL,7,Fvariable tariff (SVT) is expected to
OL,8,Fspend #127 on energy in April,
OL,9,Fcompared with #205 in March, due to a
OL,10,Fcombination of cheaper rates and lower
OL,11,Fusage as the weather warms up.
OL,13,FSome 10 million households who are on
OL,14,Fstandard variable tariffs and do not
OL,15,Fhave a smart meter have been urged to
OL,16,Fsend meter readings to their supplier
OL,17,Fthis weekend to ensure they do not
OL,18,Foverpay when the cheaper prices come
OL,19,Finto effect on April 1.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/11
