OL,3,CHousehold energy bills about to fall
OL,4,Cto lowest point in two years
OL,6,FNearly a fifth of households who do
OL,7,Fnot have a smart meter (18%) have not
OL,8,Fsubmitted their meter readings in the
OL,9,Flast three months, and 4% have not
OL,10,Fdone so for a whole year, a survey for
OL,11,Fthe comparison site found.
OL,13,FOfgem said the price cap drop would
OL,14,Fsee energy prices reach their lowest
OL,15,Flevel since Russia's invasion of
OL,16,FUkraine in February 2022, which caused
OL,17,Fa spike in an already turbulent
OL,18,Fwholesale energy market, driving up
OL,19,Fcosts for suppliers and customers.
