OL,3,CHousehold energy bills about to fall
OL,4,Cto lowest point in two years
OL,6,FMeanwhile, standing charges ` the
OL,7,Ffixed daily amount households pay to
OL,8,Fhave energy supplied to their
OL,9,Fproperty, no matter how much they use
OL,10,F` are going up.
OL,12,FFor gas, standing charges are rising
OL,13,Ffrom the average 29.6p to an average
OL,14,F31.43p a day, while the daily standing
OL,15,Fcharge for electricity will rise from
OL,16,F53.35p a day to 60.1p a day.
OL,18,FThis means that for the average direct
OL,19,Fdebit customer, a total energy bill's
OL,20,Fstanding charges will rise from #303 a
OL,21,Fyear to #334.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G8/11
