OL,3,CHousehold energy bills about to fall
OL,4,Cto lowest point in two years
OL,6,FIt is also important to note that the
OL,7,Fprice cap is not a limit on the
OL,8,Foverall amount people will pay for
OL,9,Ftheir energy, but instead caps the
OL,10,Famount that they pay per kilowatt
OL,11,Fhour, or unit, of gas and electricity.
OL,13,FSimon Francis, coordinator of the End
OL,14,FFuel Poverty Coalition, said: "As
OL,15,Fstanding charges go up, households
OL,16,Fhave to cut back on their energy use
OL,17,Fjust to keep their bills the same.
